pment.\n\nWe have for each candidate:\n\nA: anticipate dangerous situations, see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities, sometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized, unfriendly (from earlier? Actually unfriendly not listed but \"unfriendly\" appears in Agent 3 answer but not in original list. Original list: \"Candidate A can anticipate dangerous situations. Candidate A is able to see complex connections. Candidate A has excellent spatial vision. Candidate A has very good leadership qualities. Candidate A is sometimes not good at taking criticism. Candidate A can be unorganized.\" No mention of unfriendly. So we should not claim unfriendly. So we have leadership, anticipation, complex connections, spatial vision, some criticism issues, unorganized. No explicit reliability, calmness, teamwork communication (though leadership suggests some teamwork). No explicit technical competence? Spatial vision and complex connections may be technical. But we need to be careful.\n\nB: keeps calm in a crisis, 100% reliable, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills, can be grumpy, can be uncooperative. Also makes nasty remarks (from earlier). So strengths: reliability, calmness, technical (weather assessment, computer), but weaknesses: grumpy, uncooperative, nasty remarks (teamwork issues).\n\nC: can make correct decisions quickly, handles stress very well, creates a positive atmosphere with his crew, difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education. So strengths: quick decision, stress handling, crew atmosphere (teamwork), but weaknesses: communication difficulty, egocentric, lack of professional development.\n\nD: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously, regarded as arrogant, relatively weak leadership skills, hot temper (from earlier). So strengths: problem solving, concentration, responsibility, handling unexpected events, but weaknesses: arrogance, weak leadership, hot temper (calmness issues).\n\nWe need to evaluate holistically for long-distance pilot. Reliability is crucial: B is 100% reliable, D takes responsibility seriously (reliability?), A unknown, C unknown.\n\nTechnical competence: A's anticipation, complex connections, spatial vision are good; B's weather assessment, computer skills; C quick decisions; D problem solving, concentration.\n\nCalmness under pressure: B keeps calm in crisis, C handles stress well, D mixed (adequate response but hot temper), A unknown.\n\nDecision-making: C quick correct decisions, A anticipates dangerous situations (maybe proactive), D solves problems extremely well.\n\nTeamwork/communication: B negative, C positive atmosphere but communication difficulty, D arrogant, weak leadership, A leadership but unorganized, maybe not good at criticism.\n\nProfessional development: B unknown, C not willing to further education (negative), D unknown, A unknown.\n\nWe need to decide best candidate. Likely B has reliability and calmness, but teamwork issues severe. C has good stress handling and crew atmosphere but communication issues and egocentric, lack of development. D has responsibility and problem solving but hot temper and weak leadership. A has leadership but unorganized, no reliability evidence.\n\nThus B's teamwork issues may be disqualifying for long-distance crew. C's communication difficulty may be mitigated by positive atmosphere? Egocentric may be problematic. D's hot temper may be problematic. A's lack of reliability unknown.\n\nWe might ask other agents for missing info: e.g., ask Agent 2 about Candidate C's reliability or technical competence; ask Agent 3 about Candidate D's leadership strength; ask about Candidate A's teamwork/communication (maybe other agents have info). But we already asked about A's reliability and calmness; we got no info. Could ask about A's teamwork/communic